Quote:  The genus <i>Chioonochloa (chion</i> = snow;<i>chloa</i> = grass) includes the snow tussocks, or tall tussocks - up to 2 metres high - that make up the grand, golden army that dominates our subalpine grasslands, furring the hills a tawny gold and forming a magnificent backdrop for beer and car commercials.
